RIYADH: Saudi Deputy Minister for Political and Economic Affairs Eid Al-Thaqafi met South Korean Ambassador to the Kingdom Park Joon-yong on Tuesday. The duo discussed bilateral relations and ways to boost them. They also discussed issues of common interest. The two nations are expanding cooperation in diverse sectors such as healthcare, renewable and nuclear energy, smart cities, e-government, and small and medium enterprises. The two countries launched the ministerial-level Korea-Saudi Vision 2030 Committee in 2017 to boost cooperation, enhance business networking, and ensure sustainable support for the reform plan.   